      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "# User Profile Retrieval API Endpoint\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `GET /user` endpoint retrieves a user's profile information, including their username, email, and other relevant details.\n\n## Authentication\n\nThis endpoint requires Basic Authentication to ensure secure access to user data. Developers should use the `Authorization` header with a `Basic` scheme and a base64-encoded string containing the username and password.\n\n## Response\n\nThe response will be in JSON format and will include the user's profile information, such as:\n\n* `username`: The user's chosen username\n* `email`: The user's email address\n* `name`: The user's full name\n* `created_at`: The timestamp when the user account was created\n\n## Request Example\n\n```bash\nGET /user HTTP/1.1\nAuthorization: Basic <base64-encoded-username-and-password>\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe endpoint will return a 401 Unauthorized response if the authentication credentials are invalid or missing. A 404 Not Found response will be returned if the requested user is not found.\n\n## API Limitations\n\n* The endpoint is rate-limited to 10 requests per minute to prevent abuse.\n* The response will only include the user's profile information; additional fields may",
